{
  "video_id": "p4xlSRWO1Mc",
  "title": "RSA Animate - The Divided Brain",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 3000.0,
      "text": "-"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3000.0,
      "end_time": 6000.0,
      "text": "IAIN McGILCHRIST - The Divided Brain &amp; Making of the Western World"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6000.0,
      "end_time": 9000.0,
      "text": "IAIN McGILCHRIST - The Divided Brain &amp; Making of the Western World"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9000.0,
      "end_time": 12000.0,
      "text": "The division of the brain is something"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12000.0,
      "end_time": 15000.0,
      "text": "neuroscientists don&#39;t like to talk about any more."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15000.0,
      "end_time": 18000.0,
      "text": "It enjoyed a sort of popularity in the 60s and the 70s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18000.0,
      "end_time": 21000.0,
      "text": "after the first split brain operations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21000.0,
      "end_time": 24000.0,
      "text": "and it led to a sort of popularization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 24000.0,
      "end_time": 27000.0,
      "text": "which has since been proved to be"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 27000.0,
      "end_time": 30000.0,
      "text": "entirely false! And it&#39;s not true"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 30000.0,
      "end_time": 33000.0,
      "text": "that one part of the brain does reason,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 33000.0,
      "end_time": 36000.0,
      "text": "and the other does emotion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 36000.0,
      "end_time": 39000.0,
      "text": "both are profoundly involved in both. It&#39;s not true"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 39000.0,
      "end_time": 42000.0,
      "text": "that language resides only in the left HMP,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 42000.0,
      "end_time": 45000.0,
      "text": "it doesn&#39;t. Important aspects are in the right."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 45000.0,
      "end_time": 48000.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not true that visual imagery is only in the right HMP,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 48000.0,
      "end_time": 51000.0,
      "text": "lots of it is in the left. And so, in a sort of fit of despair"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 51000.0,
      "end_time": 54000.0,
      "text": "people have given up talking about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 54000.0,
      "end_time": 57000.0,
      "text": "But the problem won&#39;t really go away! Because this organ,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 57000.0,
      "end_time": 60000.0,
      "text": "which is all about making connection is profoundly DIVIDED!"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 60000.0,
      "end_time": 63000.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s there inside all of us, and it&#39;s got more divided"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 63000.0,
      "end_time": 66000.0,
      "text": "over the course of human evolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 66000.0,
      "end_time": 69000.0,
      "text": "So the ratio of the corpus callosum"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 69000.0,
      "end_time": 72000.0,
      "text": "to the volume of the HMP has got smaller"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 72000.0,
      "end_time": 75000.0,
      "text": "over the evolution. And the flot thickens"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 75000.0,
      "end_time": 78000.0,
      "text": "when you realize that one of the main, if not THE MAIN"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 78000.0,
      "end_time": 81000.0,
      "text": "function of the corpus callosum is in fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 81000.0,
      "end_time": 84000.0,
      "text": "to INHIBIT the other hemisphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 84000.0,
      "end_time": 87000.0,
      "text": "So something very important is going on here"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 87000.0,
      "end_time": 90000.0,
      "text": "by keeping things apart from one another."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 90000.0,
      "end_time": 93000.0,
      "text": "And not only that: the brain is profoundly a simmetric"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 93000.0,
      "end_time": 96000.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s broader at the back on the left,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 96000.0,
      "end_time": 99000.0,
      "text": "and broader on the right of the front on the side"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 99000.0,
      "end_time": 102000.0,
      "text": "leans just forward and backward and if it&#39;s though somebody"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 102000.0,
      "end_time": 105000.0,
      "text": "got hold of the brain from underneath and given it just a sharp twist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 105000.0,
      "end_time": 108000.0,
      "text": "clockwise. What is all that about?"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 108000.0,
      "end_time": 111000.0,
      "text": "If one just needed more brains space, one would do it simmetrically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 111000.0,
      "end_time": 114000.0,
      "text": "the skull is simmetrical. The box in which all this is contained is simmetrical."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 114000.0,
      "end_time": 117000.0,
      "text": "Why goes the trouble to expand some bits of one HMP,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 117000.0,
      "end_time": 120000.0,
      "text": "and some bits of another, unless they are doing rather different things."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 120000.0,
      "end_time": 123000.0,
      "text": "What are they doing? Well it&#39;s not just we, who have these"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 123000.0,
      "end_time": 126000.0,
      "text": "divided brains: birds and animals have them as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 126000.0,
      "end_time": 129000.0,
      "text": "I think the simplest way to think of it is"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 129000.0,
      "end_time": 132000.0,
      "text": "to imagine a bird trying to feed on a seed"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 132000.0,
      "end_time": 135000.0,
      "text": "against the background of grit or pebbles."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 135000.0,
      "end_time": 138000.0,
      "text": "It has got to focus very narrowly"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 138000.0,
      "end_time": 141000.0,
      "text": "and clearly on that little seed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 141000.0,
      "end_time": 144000.0,
      "text": "and be able to pick it out against that background."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 144000.0,
      "end_time": 147000.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s also -if it&#39;s going to stay alive-"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 147000.0,
      "end_time": 150000.0,
      "text": "it has got to actually keep a quite different kind of attention open,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 150000.0,
      "end_time": 153000.0,
      "text": "it has got to be on the look out for predators,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 153000.0,
      "end_time": 156000.0,
      "text": "or for friends...specifics, but for whatever else is going on."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 156000.0,
      "end_time": 159000.0,
      "text": "It seems those birds"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 159000.0,
      "end_time": 162000.0,
      "text": "and animals quite reliably"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 162000.0,
      "end_time": 165000.0,
      "text": "use their left HMP for this narrow focused attention,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 165000.0,
      "end_time": 168000.0,
      "text": "something it already knows"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 168000.0,
      "end_time": 171000.0,
      "text": "is of importance to it. And they keep their right HMP"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 171000.0,
      "end_time": 174000.0,
      "text": "vigilant broadly for whatever might be without"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 174000.0,
      "end_time": 177000.0,
      "text": "any commitment as to what that might be. And they also use"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 177000.0,
      "end_time": 180000.0,
      "text": "their right HMPs for making conenctions with the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 180000.0,
      "end_time": 183000.0,
      "text": "So they approach their mates, and bond to"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 183000.0,
      "end_time": 186000.0,
      "text": "their mates more using their right HMP."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 186000.0,
      "end_time": 189000.0,
      "text": "But then you come to the humans, and it&#39;s true"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 189000.0,
      "end_time": 192000.0,
      "text": "that actually in humans, too, this kind of attention"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 192000.0,
      "end_time": 195000.0,
      "text": "is one fo the big differences."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 195000.0,
      "end_time": 198000.0,
      "text": "The right HMP gives sustained, broad,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 198000.0,
      "end_time": 201000.0,
      "text": "open vigilance, alertness."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 201000.0,
      "end_time": 204000.0,
      "text": "Where the left HMP gives narrow, sharply focused"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 204000.0,
      "end_time": 207000.0,
      "text": "attention to details. And people who loose"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 207000.0,
      "end_time": 210000.0,
      "text": "their right HMPs have a pathological narrowing"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 210000.0,
      "end_time": 213000.0,
      "text": "of the window of attention."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 213000.0,
      "end_time": 216000.0,
      "text": "But humans are different. The big thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 216000.0,
      "end_time": 219000.0,
      "text": "about humans is their frontal lobes."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 219000.0,
      "end_time": 222000.0,
      "text": "And the purpose of that part of the brain to inhibit:"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 222000.0,
      "end_time": 225000.0,
      "text": "to inhibit the rest of the brain, to stop"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 225000.0,
      "end_time": 228000.0,
      "text": "the immediate happening;"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 228000.0,
      "end_time": 231000.0,
      "text": "so standing back in time and space from the immediacy"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 231000.0,
      "end_time": 234000.0,
      "text": "of experience. And that enables us to do two things:"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 234000.0,
      "end_time": 237000.0,
      "text": "it enables us to do - what neuroscientists"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 237000.0,
      "end_time": 240000.0,
      "text": "are always telling us we are very good at - which is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 240000.0,
      "end_time": 243000.0,
      "text": "outwitting the other party, being Machiavellian."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 243000.0,
      "end_time": 246000.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s interesting to me, because"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 246000.0,
      "end_time": 249000.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s absolutely right: we can read other people&#39;s minds"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 249000.0,
      "end_time": 252000.0,
      "text": "and intentions, and if we so want to, we can deceive them."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 252000.0,
      "end_time": 255000.0,
      "text": "But the bit that&#39;s always curiosity missed out here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 255000.0,
      "end_time": 258000.0,
      "text": "is this: it also enables us"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 258000.0,
      "end_time": 261000.0,
      "text": "to empathize for the first time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 261000.0,
      "end_time": 264000.0,
      "text": "because this is sort of necessary distance from the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 264000.0,
      "end_time": 267000.0,
      "text": "And if you&#39;re right up against it, it just bites,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 267000.0,
      "end_time": 270000.0,
      "text": "but if you can stand back and see, that other individual is"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 270000.0,
      "end_time": 273000.0,
      "text": "an individual like me, who might have interests"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 273000.0,
      "end_time": 276000.0,
      "text": "and values and feelings like mine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 276000.0,
      "end_time": 279000.0,
      "text": "then you can make a bond, this is sort of necessary distance"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 279000.0,
      "end_time": 282000.0,
      "text": "as there is in reading, too close - you can&#39;t see anything;"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 282000.0,
      "end_time": 285000.0,
      "text": "too far - can&#39;t read it."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 285000.0,
      "end_time": 288000.0,
      "text": "So the distance from the world that is provided"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 288000.0,
      "end_time": 291000.0,
      "text": "is profoundly creative of all that is human,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 291000.0,
      "end_time": 294000.0,
      "text": "both in Machiavellian and the Erasmian."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 294000.0,
      "end_time": 297000.0,
      "text": "Now, to do the Machiavellian stuff,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 297000.0,
      "end_time": 300000.0,
      "text": "to manipulate the world - which is very important - we need to be able to use,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 300000.0,
      "end_time": 303000.0,
      "text": "interact with the world and use it for our benefit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 303000.0,
      "end_time": 306000.0,
      "text": "-food is the starting point-"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 306000.0,
      "end_time": 309000.0,
      "text": "but, we also with our left HMP grasp, using our"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 309000.0,
      "end_time": 312000.0,
      "text": "right hands, things and make tools,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 312000.0,
      "end_time": 315000.0,
      "text": "we also use that part of the language"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 315000.0,
      "end_time": 318000.0,
      "text": "to grasp things as we say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 318000.0,
      "end_time": 321000.0,
      "text": "it &#39;pins&#39; them down. So when we already know something&#39;s important,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 321000.0,
      "end_time": 324000.0,
      "text": "and we want to be precise about it, we use our left HMPs"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 324000.0,
      "end_time": 327000.0,
      "text": "in that way. And to do that we need a simplified"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 327000.0,
      "end_time": 330000.0,
      "text": "version of reality. It&#39;s no good, if you&#39;re"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 330000.0,
      "end_time": 333000.0,
      "text": "fighting a campaign, having all the information"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 333000.0,
      "end_time": 336000.0,
      "text": "on all the plant species that grow in the"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 336000.0,
      "end_time": 339000.0,
      "text": "terrain of battle. What you need"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 339000.0,
      "end_time": 342000.0,
      "text": "is to know the specifics of where certain things are, that matter to you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 342000.0,
      "end_time": 345000.0,
      "text": "and so you have a map, and you have little flags."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 345000.0,
      "end_time": 348000.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not reality, but it works BETTER."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 348000.0,
      "end_time": 351000.0,
      "text": "The newness of the right HMP makes it"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 351000.0,
      "end_time": 354000.0,
      "text": "the devil&#39;s advocat: is always on the look out"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 354000.0,
      "end_time": 357000.0,
      "text": "for things that might be different from our expectations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 357000.0,
      "end_time": 360000.0,
      "text": "it sees things in context, it understands implicit meaning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 360000.0,
      "end_time": 363000.0,
      "text": "metaphor, body language, emotional expression on the face."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 363000.0,
      "end_time": 366000.0,
      "text": "It deals with an EMBODIED WORLD, in which we stand"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 366000.0,
      "end_time": 369000.0,
      "text": "embodied in relation to a world that is CONCRETE."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 369000.0,
      "end_time": 372000.0,
      "text": "It understands individuals, not just categories."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 372000.0,
      "end_time": 375000.0,
      "text": "It actually has a disposition for the living, rather than the mechanical."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 375000.0,
      "end_time": 378000.0,
      "text": "And this is so marked,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 378000.0,
      "end_time": 381000.0,
      "text": "that even in the left hand though, who is actually using their"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 381000.0,
      "end_time": 384000.0,
      "text": "right HMPs in daily lifes to manipulate the tools with their left hand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 384000.0,
      "end_time": 387000.0,
      "text": "it is their left HMP, not the right HMP, in which"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 387000.0,
      "end_time": 390000.0,
      "text": "tools and machines are coded. So this is very interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 390000.0,
      "end_time": 393000.0,
      "text": "And it changes the view of the body: the body becomes"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 393000.0,
      "end_time": 396000.0,
      "text": "an assemblage of parts in the left HMP."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 396000.0,
      "end_time": 399000.0,
      "text": "If I had to sum this all up, I would"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 399000.0,
      "end_time": 402000.0,
      "text": "get away from all those things that we used to say:"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 402000.0,
      "end_time": 405000.0,
      "text": "reason and imagination. Let me make you very clear:"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 405000.0,
      "end_time": 408000.0,
      "text": "for IMAGINATION you need BOTH HMPs."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 408000.0,
      "end_time": 411000.0,
      "text": "Let me make you very clear: for REASON you need BOTH HMPs."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 411000.0,
      "end_time": 414000.0,
      "text": "So if I had to sum this up, I&#39;d take the world of the left HMP dependant on"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 414000.0,
      "end_time": 417000.0,
      "text": "DENOTATIVE LANGUAGE and ABSTRACTION,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 417000.0,
      "end_time": 420000.0,
      "text": "YIELDS CLARITY and power to manipulate things"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 420000.0,
      "end_time": 423000.0,
      "text": "that are KNOWN, FIXED, STATIC, ISOLATED,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 423000.0,
      "end_time": 426000.0,
      "text": "DECONTEXTUALIZED, EXPLICIT,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 426000.0,
      "end_time": 429000.0,
      "text": "GENERAL IN NATURE, but ultimately LIFELESS."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 429000.0,
      "end_time": 432000.0,
      "text": "The right HMP by contrast yields a WORLD OF"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 432000.0,
      "end_time": 435000.0,
      "text": "INDIVIDUAL, CHANGING, EVOLVING,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 435000.0,
      "end_time": 438000.0,
      "text": "INTERCONNECTED, IMPLICIT, INCARNATE"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 438000.0,
      "end_time": 441000.0,
      "text": "LIVING BEINGS WITHIN THE CONTEXT of the lived world."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 441000.0,
      "end_time": 444000.0,
      "text": "But the nature fot things is never fully graspable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 444000.0,
      "end_time": 447000.0,
      "text": "never perfectly known, and this world exists"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 447000.0,
      "end_time": 450000.0,
      "text": "in a certain relationship. The knowledge that is mediated by the"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 450000.0,
      "end_time": 453000.0,
      "text": "left HMP is however within a closed system."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 453000.0,
      "end_time": 456000.0,
      "text": "It has the advantage of perfection, but the perfection"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 456000.0,
      "end_time": 459000.0,
      "text": "has brought ultimately the price of emptiness."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 459000.0,
      "end_time": 462000.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a problem here about the nature"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 462000.0,
      "end_time": 465000.0,
      "text": "of the two worlds. The offer is the two versions of the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 465000.0,
      "end_time": 468000.0,
      "text": "and obviously we combine them in different ways all the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 468000.0,
      "end_time": 471000.0,
      "text": "We need to rely on certain things to manipulate the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 471000.0,
      "end_time": 474000.0,
      "text": "but for the broad understanding of it we need"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 474000.0,
      "end_time": 477000.0,
      "text": "to use knowledge that comes from the right HMP."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 477000.0,
      "end_time": 480000.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s my suggestion to you that in the history if western culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 480000.0,
      "end_time": 483000.0,
      "text": "things started in 6th century of B.C. in the Augustian era,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 483000.0,
      "end_time": 486000.0,
      "text": "and in the 15th/16th century in Europe"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 486000.0,
      "end_time": 489000.0,
      "text": "with a wonderful balancing of these HMPs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 489000.0,
      "end_time": 492000.0,
      "text": "in each cases it drifted further"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 492000.0,
      "end_time": 495000.0,
      "text": "to the left HMP&#39;s point of view."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 495000.0,
      "end_time": 498000.0,
      "text": "Nowadays we live in a world which is paradoxical."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 498000.0,
      "end_time": 501000.0,
      "text": "We pursue HAPINESS,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 501000.0,
      "end_time": 504000.0,
      "text": "and it leads to RESENTMENT, and it leads to UNHAPPINESS,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 504000.0,
      "end_time": 507000.0,
      "text": "and it leads in fact to an explosion of MENTAL ILLNESS."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 507000.0,
      "end_time": 510000.0,
      "text": "We pursued FREEDOM, but we now live in a world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 510000.0,
      "end_time": 513000.0,
      "text": "which is more monitored, by CCTV cameras,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 513000.0,
      "end_time": 516000.0,
      "text": "and in which our daily lives are more subjected"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 516000.0,
      "end_time": 519000.0,
      "text": "to what the top ? called a network of"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 519000.0,
      "end_time": 522000.0,
      "text": "small complicated rules that cover"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 522000.0,
      "end_time": 525000.0,
      "text": "the surface of life and strangle freedom."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 525000.0,
      "end_time": 528000.0,
      "text": "More information - we have it in spate"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 528000.0,
      "end_time": 531000.0,
      "text": "but we can less and less able to use it"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 531000.0,
      "end_time": 534000.0,
      "text": "to understand it, to be wise."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 534000.0,
      "end_time": 537000.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a paradoxical relationship as I know as a psychiatrist"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 537000.0,
      "end_time": 540000.0,
      "text": "between ADVERSITY and FULFILMENT;"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 540000.0,
      "end_time": 543000.0,
      "text": "between RESTRAINT and FREEDOM,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 543000.0,
      "end_time": 546000.0,
      "text": "between the KNOWLEDGE of the PARTS, and WISDOM of the WHOLE."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 546000.0,
      "end_time": 549000.0,
      "text": "The machine model again, that is supposed to answer everything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 549000.0,
      "end_time": 552000.0,
      "text": "but it doesn&#39;t; think about this: even RATIONALITY"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 552000.0,
      "end_time": 554000.0,
      "text": "is grounded in a leap of INTUITION."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 554000.0,
      "end_time": 557000.0,
      "text": "There is NEVER you can rationally prove,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 557000.0,
      "end_time": 560000.0,
      "text": "that rationality is a good way to look at the world. We intuit that this is very helpful."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 560000.0,
      "end_time": 563000.0,
      "text": "And this is not new. At the other end of the process"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 563000.0,
      "end_time": 566000.0,
      "text": "rationality, we know from Gödel&#39;s theorum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 566000.0,
      "end_time": 569000.0,
      "text": "we know from what Pascal was saying hundreds of years before Gödel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 569000.0,
      "end_time": 572000.0,
      "text": "that at the end point of rationality is to demonstrate the limits to rationality."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 572000.0,
      "end_time": 575000.0,
      "text": "In our modern world we&#39;ve developed something"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 575000.0,
      "end_time": 578000.0,
      "text": "that looks awfully alike the left HMP&#39;s world:"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 578000.0,
      "end_time": 581000.0,
      "text": "we prioritize the VIRTUAL over the REAL."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 581000.0,
      "end_time": 584000.0,
      "text": "The TECHNICAL becomes important, BUREUCRACY flourishes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 584000.0,
      "end_time": 587000.0,
      "text": "the picture however is fragmented."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 587000.0,
      "end_time": 590000.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a lot of uniqueness. The HOW has become subsumed in WHAT."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 590000.0,
      "end_time": 593000.0,
      "text": "And the need for control leads to a paranoia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 593000.0,
      "end_time": 596000.0,
      "text": "in society, that we need to govern and control everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 596000.0,
      "end_time": 599000.0,
      "text": "Why is this shift? I think there are 3 reasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 599000.0,
      "end_time": 602000.0,
      "text": "One is: the left HMP&#39;s talk"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 602000.0,
      "end_time": 605000.0,
      "text": "is very convincing, because it shaped everything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 605000.0,
      "end_time": 608000.0,
      "text": "that it doesn&#39;t find fit for this model: OFF!"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 608000.0,
      "end_time": 611000.0,
      "text": "And cut it out. So this particular model is"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 611000.0,
      "end_time": 614000.0,
      "text": "entirely self-consistent, largely &#39;cause it&#39;s made itself so."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 614000.0,
      "end_time": 617000.0,
      "text": "I also call the left HMP the Berlusconi"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 617000.0,
      "end_time": 620000.0,
      "text": "of the brain, because it controls the media,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 620000.0,
      "end_time": 623000.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s the one with which we..."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 623000.0,
      "end_time": 626000.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s very vocal on its own behalf."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 626000.0,
      "end_time": 629000.0,
      "text": "The right HMP doesn&#39;t have a voice, and it"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 629000.0,
      "end_time": 632000.0,
      "text": "can&#39;t construct these same arguments."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 632000.0,
      "end_time": 635000.0,
      "text": "And I also think - rather more importantly - this is sort of &#39;hall of mirrors&#39; effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 635000.0,
      "end_time": 638000.0,
      "text": "The more we get trapped into this, the more we undercut and ironize"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 638000.0,
      "end_time": 641000.0,
      "text": "things that might have led us out of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 641000.0,
      "end_time": 644000.0,
      "text": "and we just get reflected back: the more we know about what we know about..."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 644000.0,
      "end_time": 647000.0,
      "text": "And just to make you clear: I am not AGAINST"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 647000.0,
      "end_time": 650000.0,
      "text": "whatever it is the left HMP has to offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 650000.0,
      "end_time": 653000.0,
      "text": "Nobody could be more compassionate in an age in which we neglect reason,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 653000.0,
      "end_time": 656000.0,
      "text": "and we neglect careful use of language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 656000.0,
      "end_time": 659000.0,
      "text": "nobody could be more passionate than myself about language"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 659000.0,
      "end_time": 662000.0,
      "text": "and about reason, it&#39;s just that I am even more passionate"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 662000.0,
      "end_time": 665000.0,
      "text": "about the right HMP, and the need to return"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 665000.0,
      "end_time": 668000.0,
      "text": "what that knows: to a broader context."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 668000.0,
      "end_time": 671000.0,
      "text": "It turned out, that Einstein&#39;s thinking"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 671000.0,
      "end_time": 674000.0,
      "text": "somehow presage this thing about the structure of the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 674000.0,
      "end_time": 677000.0,
      "text": "He said: &quot;The intuitive mind"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 677000.0,
      "end_time": 680000.0,
      "text": "is a sacred gift, and the rational mind"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 680000.0,
      "end_time": 683000.0,
      "text": "is a faithful servant. We have created a society"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 683000.0,
      "end_time": 686000.0,
      "text": "that honours the servant, but has forgotten"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 686000.0,
      "end_time": 689000.0,
      "text": "the gift.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 689000.0,
      "end_time": 692000.0,
      "text": "-"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 692000.0,
      "end_time": 695000.0,
      "text": "-"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 695000.0,
      "end_time": 698000.0,
      "text": "-"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 698000.0,
      "end_time": 701000.0,
      "text": "-"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 701000.0,
      "end_time": 704000.0,
      "text": "-"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 704000.0,
      "end_time": 707000.0,
      "text": "-"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 707000.0,
      "end_time": 710000.0,
      "text": "-"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 710000.0,
      "end_time": 720000.0,
      "text": "."
    }
  ]
}